    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Areas of a town or city designed for, zoned for, or used primarily by stores and other establishments selling goods. Characteristics may include sections that are open only to pedestrian traffic, adequate parking facilities for automobiles, and other features that attract shoppers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>鄉鎮城市中設計、劃分或主要用途為提供商店或其他店家銷售商品的區域。此區的特色可能包括行人專用區、充足的停車設施，以及其他可供吸引購物人潮的機能。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gebiet innerhalb einer Kleinstadt oder Stadt, das konzipiert, abgegrenzt und vorranging verwendet wird für Läden und andere Einrichtungen, die Waren verkaufen. Die Merkmale eines Einkaufsviertels können Abschnitte, die nur für Fußgängerverkehr geöffnet sind, ausreichende Parkmöglichkeiten für Autos und andere Ausstattungen einschließen, die Käufer anzieht.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Áreas de uma cidade ou cidade projetadas, divididas em zonas ou usadas principalmente por lojas e outros estabelecimentos que vendem mercadorias. As características podem incluir seções que são abertas apenas ao tráfego de pedestres, estacionamento adequado para automóveis e outros recursos que atraem compradores.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
